p.k: Charlotte Huxley (Alison Rey) is an ambitious young woman who's vying for a contract with the big graphic design firm, Cambridge House. In her first meeting for an exciting new project, she runs into her old nemesis from college, Tucker Grant (Seth Gamble). Charlotte is dismayed but Tucker is determined to prove to her that he's a different man from the one she knew. However Tucker's ruthless assistant Candy (Jane Wilde) comes up with a plan to win them the book cover, but it would destroy Tucker's chances with Charlotte forever. Will Tucker choose his career over the woman he loves? A sexy office drama with a whirlwind of dynamic characters and passionate encounters, Graphic Content is sure to make you believe in second chances.
